    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2433" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δίσκος</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δικεῖν</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">discus, quoit</span>, of metal or
          stone.—Hence <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δίσκουρα</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οὖρον</span>), n. pl., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">a quoit's
          cast</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.431</span></i>, 523. —(For
          the attitude in throwing the quoit, see cut, after Myron's famous
          statue of the Discobolus.) 
